</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsect1>
<title>Filing a bug report or feature request</title>

<para>
If you encounter a bug, misfeature, or missing feature in libgretl, please
file a bug report or feature request at
<ulink url="http://sourceforge.net/tracker/?group_id=36234">sourceforge.net</ulink>.
</para>

</refsect1>

<refsect1>
<title>Mailing lists</title>

<para>
There are two main mailing lists dedicated to gretl.
</para>

<para>
<variablelist>

<varlistentry>
<term><ulink url="http://lists.wfu.edu/mailman/listinfo/gretl-users">gretl-users@lists.wfu.edu</ulink></term>
<listitem><para>
gretl-users covers general gretl topics from the standpoint of users of the programs
<application>gretl</application> and <application>gretlcli</application>.
</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term><ulink url="http://lists.wfu.edu/mailman/listinfo/gretl-devel">gretl-devel@lists.wfu.edu</ulink></term>
<listitem><para>
gretl-devel-list is for discussion of work on gretl itself. It is 
<emphasis>not</emphasis> for asking questions about how to use gretl,
but is (for the present) the right place for asking questions about developing
and running programs that use libgretl.
</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>
</para>

</refsect1>


